					<description><![CDATA[Thank you for the clear explanation! A common mistake I used to make was using a semicolon before a list, not in it. It felt less bold than a colon; when I was unsure, bold seemed risky.  To those making slurs and speaking about using punctuation as pretentious, I am sorry you feel that people who can google the correct way to use a semicolon are better than you. Remember this, it just isn&#039;t true, yes they can wield a sentence better than you can, but that doesn&#039;t make them a better person than you. Also, if you are feeling inferior, practice makes perfect, and you have great writing blogs like this to help, so you don&#039;t have to feel alone either.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Thank you for the clear explanation! A common mistake I used to make was using a semicolon before a list, not in it. It felt less bold than a colon; when I was unsure, bold seemed risky.  To those making slurs and speaking about using punctuation as pretentious, I am sorry you feel that people who can google the correct way to use a semicolon are better than you. Remember this, it just isn&#8217;t true, yes they can wield a sentence better than you can, but that doesn&#8217;t make them a better person than you. Also, if you are feeling inferior, practice makes perfect, and you have great writing blogs like this to help, so you don&#8217;t have to feel alone either.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
