<p>You just used &#8220;however, as a young girl&#8230;&#8221; in the first sentence, when that was the perfect opportunity to use the semi colon&#8230; .<br />
For example, &#8220;I do not have extensive college training; however, as a young girl growing up with my parents and siblings in the Caribbean (where my mother was a book-worm and my father a stickler for the so-called ‘Queens English’ ), not only did I practice speaking proper English consistently, but read and wrote a whole lot.</p>
