					<description><![CDATA[Strange. I would never consider this usage pretentious at all:

&quot;The council is John Smith, president; Alison Peterson, vice president; Bruce Jeffries, secretary; and Marilyn Ehrmantraut, treasurer.&quot;

In my opinion, without using semicolons there, it can get confusing. I don&#039;t find that pretentious (or too much effort) at all.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Strange. I would never consider this usage pretentious at all:</p>
<p>&#8220;The council is John Smith, president; Alison Peterson, vice president; Bruce Jeffries, secretary; and Marilyn Ehrmantraut, treasurer.&#8221;</p>
<p>In my opinion, without using semicolons there, it can get confusing. I don&#8217;t find that pretentious (or too much effort) at all.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
